1 (8) [(i)] Require that a child care center have in attendance at all times
2 at least 1 individual who is responsible for supervision of children, including children on
3 field trips, and who holds a current certificate indicating successful completion of approved:
4 [1.] (I) Basic first aid training through the American Red
5 Cross or through a program with equivalent standards; and
6 [2.] (II) Cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) training
7 through the American Heart Association or through a program with equivalent standards
8 appropriate for the ages of children for whom care is provided in the child care center; [and
9 (ii) Require that a child care center serving more than 20 children
10 have in attendance certificate holders described in item (i) of this item in a ratio of at least
11 1 certificate holder for every 20 children;]
12 (9) Require that the minimum age of a child care teacher in a child care
13 center be at least 18 years old and an individual may not be precluded from being a child
14 care teacher solely for being 18 years old;
15 (10) (i) Require that a child care center that receives notice of a
16 contaminated drinking water supply from the child care center’s supplier of water, in
17 accordance with § 9–410 of the Environment Article or otherwise, send notice of the
18 drinking water contamination to the parent or legal guardian of each child attending the
19 child care center; and
20 (ii) Require that the notice sent by the child care center shall:
21 1. Be sent within 10 business days after receipt of the notice
22 of contamination from the child care center’s water supplier;
23 2. Be in writing;
24 3. Identify the contaminants and their levels in the center’s
25 water supply; and
26 4. Describe the child care center’s plan for dealing with the
27 water contamination problem until the child care center’s water is determined by the
28 appropriate authority to be safe for consumption;
29 (11) (i) Require a child care center to have a written emergency
30 preparedness plan for emergency situations that require evacuation, sheltering in place, or
31 other protection of children, such as in the event of fire, natural disaster, or other
32 threatening situation that may pose a health or safety hazard to the children in the child
33 care center;
34 (ii) Require the plan under item (i) of this item to include:

